    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen doing a substitute with the /c flag, I can’t tell where the cursor/what the current replacement target is. I can fix this by reassigning `:hi! IncSearch guibg=Red` or another colour, so the current replacement is visible.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim —clean\r\ninsert `foobar` on several lines\r\n:%s/foobar/replacement/gc\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCurrent confirm location is visible, don’t really care what colour we use!\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nHEAD\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMint\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty 0.12\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nsource",
